e of Love.\nSCENE OF RICH\nSTRIKE\n(From Tuesday's Dally)\nMore gold excitement was caused\nyesterday when it became kuown that\na rich strike had been made hi an old\nabandoned mine on .Spring Creek, sev\nenty-five miles north of Globe, und that\nthere was 11 rush of men into the coun\ntry from Hoosevclt ami other nearby\npoints us soon us the rumors of the\nshrike leaked out, sars thu Globe .Sil\nver licit.\n.Samples of the ore brought to Globn\nby a prospector named Shoemaker, who\nmade the find, ussayed $554 to the ton.\nThey run 27.7 oz. gold und 8.9 oz. sll-\nzrr. Shoemaker wns very much excited\nund left yestcrduy inorniuir for tho\ntamp, taking ten men with him to put\nto work in the mine.\nThe discovery was made in nu aban\ndoned mine on the Spring Creek ranch,,\na mile and 11 half from tho creek. The\nvein starts in uenr tho top of a .1.ri\nfoot sliuft und at thu bottom St Is a\ngootl eighteen incites ncross. Shoe\nmaker says the inluo has been aban\ndoned for over twenty years.\nHhocmnker nnd another prospector\nnamed Irbey were grub staked by W.\nABANDONED\nMINE\nAre now ready for distribution from the\nJOURNAL-MINER OFFICE.\nThis book is a complete edition of the\nLaws of\nII. Muyer of Globe, five weeks ajj\nThey went into the .Spring Crook couj.l\ntry, where there are n number of aht&.\ndotied mines, nnd began prospect!,!\nMonday .Shoemaker returned and show. I\ntvd .Mayer the ore samples which rai\nfVl to the ton.\nThe prospector says the country t\nfast filling with men and that soveri\neastern mining syndicates aro getting\nhold of coiisiilenruie property and iru\nbringing in machinery from Rootj.1\nvolt.\nMayer and tho two prospectors hav\nu lease 611 the property.\nBOUGH TRIP FROM SAN PKDR0.\n(CoBtiauid from Page Om.)\nTho fleet will said for San Francis;)\nat II p, in. tomorrow and will anchor c(\nthe Lightship cntrunco to the OoMh\nGate until tho next morning.\nThe first train on tho way to tit I\nbarbecue provided for tho officer! oil\nthe flee